[ctns_make id='axCommuteQ4-1']

    [ctns_question style='width:70%;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;']
TMPL_QUESTIONBLOCK
    [/ctns_question]
    
    [ctns_script type='script']
        var associativity = [
            "(%s \cdot %s) \cdot %s = %s \cdot (%s \cdot %s)"
            ];

        var iterations = 10;
        do {
            a = natural();
            b = natural();
            c = natural();
        } while (is_gt(iterations--, 0) && ((a === b) || (b === c) || (a === c)));

        symbols.eq = associativity.ctns_rand().ctns_format( [String(a), String(b), String(c), String(a), String(b), String(c)] );

        q.push(tex({'symbols':symbols, 'reveal':'hide', 'system':'katex'},'
The equation below demonstrates that multiplication for natural numbers is commutative. $| ${eq} |$
')); 
    
        r.push(tex({'symbols':symbols, 'reveal':'hide', 'system':'katex'},'
Multiplication for natural numbers is associative for any three natural numbers $$a,$$ $$b,$$ and $$c,$$ $|(a \cdot b) \cdot c = a \cdot (b \cdot c).|$ Multiplication for natural numbers is commutative for any two natural numbers $$a$$ and $$b$$, $|a \cdot b = b \cdot a.|$
')); 

        w.push(tex({'symbols':symbols, 'reveal':'hide', 'system':'katex'},'
To answer this question you must first know for natural numbers under multiplication both the <strong>property of commutativity</strong> AND the <strong>property of associativity</strong>. Remember that the property of commutativity says you can swap the order of multiplication and get the same sum for any two natural numbers $$a$$ and $$b$$, $|a \cdot b = b \cdot a;|$ and, for the property of associativity you can change the parentheses for any three natural numbers $$a$$, $$b$$, and $$c$$ and still get the same sum, $|(a \cdot b) \cdot c = a \cdot (b \cdot c).|$
')); 

        $(qblock).html(q.join(' '));
        $(rightblock).html(r.join(' '));
        $(wrongblock).html(w.join(' '));
        $(undecidedblock).html(w.join(' '));
    [/ctns_script]
    
    [ctns_element type='build_a_graph' swap_a_b='true'][/ctns_element]

[/ctns_make]
